io.reinert.requestor.core

Class Session

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.reinert.requestor.core.Session
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DirectInvoker, FilterManager, HasHeaders, HasRequestOptions, InterceptorManager, ProviderManager, SerializerManager
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GwtSession

    public class Session
extends Object
implements SerializerManager, FilterManager, InterceptorManager, ProviderManager, DirectInvoker, HasRequestOptions
    This is a configurable client session responsible for building requests. Usually, you will use it as a singleton.

    It provides a convenience API for managing/creating HTTP Requests.

    You can register RequestFilter or ResponseFilter, to manipulate all your requests.

    You can register RequestInterceptor or ResponseInterceptor to intercept every request/response and modify their payloads.

    You can register Serializer or a Deserializer to provide both serialization and/or deserialization of objects according to media-types. You can quickly send requests using the HTTP methods.
    Author:
    Danilo Reinert
